Day1

<!DOCTYPE html>
Tells browser the document type (HTML5 here).
<html lang="en">
Root of the HTML document.

lang="en" = means content is in English.

<head>
Container for meta info (not shown directly on page).

<meta charset="UTF-8">
Sets character encoding (UTF-8 supports most languages & symbols).

<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
Makes page responsive on mobile (scales content properly).

<title>Document</title>
Title shown in browser tab.

</head>
Ends the head section.

<body>
Contains the actual content (text, images, links, etc.) visible on the webpage.

</body>
</html>
Closes body and HTML document.